=== Etymology ===

from Greek word ''kryos'', "icy cold"

=== Definition ===

''Cryonics'' is the [[cryopreservation]] of a recently [[deceased]] person until the [[preservation]] process can be [[reverse]]d and the cause of the [[fatal]] [[disease]] can be cured (including the disease known as [[aging]]).

